    "As AI transforms nutrition and food manufacturing, it brings forth a spectrum of ethical considerations, ranging from the protection of personal data and equitable algorithmic design to workforce implications and ecological sustainability.",
    "Addressing these challenges is essential to ensure that AI adoption advances public health, equity, and sustainability.",
    "Managing sensitive health and dietary data remains a core concern in AI-based nutrition systems.",
    "Given the deeply personal nature of such data, ensuring robust safeguards against breaches and misuse is imperative.",
